Dear colleagues,=20





It is our pleasure to announce the organization of the 1st VIVA European Su=
mmer School on Artificial Intelligence and Software Verification and Valida=
tion.=20




=C2=B7 Location: Belambra Club, La Grande Motte, Montpellier, France.=20

=C2=B7 Dates: June 15-19, 2020=20

=C2=B7 Organizers: Arnaud Gotlieb (Simula Research Laboratory, Oslo), Nadji=
b Lazaar (LIRMM, University of Montpellier) and Florent Masseglia (LIRMM, I=
nria).=20

=C2=B7 Website: http://www.lirmm.fr/viva2020/=20




Facing the challenge of building trustworthy AI-based software and systems,=
 Europe needs to educate a new generation of bright researchers on the usag=
e of AI in Software Verification and Validation (V&V) and the V&V aspects o=
f AI systems. To reach this goal, we propose to welcome about 30 PhD studen=
ts in VIVA, the 1st summer school dedicated to AI and Software V&V. High-le=
vel courses will be given by the most recognized European researchers in th=
e field of Software V&V and trustworthy Artificial Intelligence and will in=
clude an appropriate combination of theoretical and practical matters. The =
courses will cover a broad spectrum of research topics including Machine Le=
arning and Data Mining in Software Testing, V&V of Neural Networks, Constra=
int Programming in Verification Testing of Autonomous Systems, etc. The PhD=
 School is co-organized by LIRMM, Simula Research Laboratory and Inria with=
 the financial support of the French Institute in Norway, Simula, Inria and=
 CNRS through the GDR-IA, GDR-MADICS and the GDR-GPL.=20




Confirmed speakers:=20

=C2=B7 S=C3=A9bastien Bardin (CEA, Paris, France)=20

=C2=B7 Christian Bessiere (CNRS, Montpellier, France)=20

=C2=B7 Catherine Dubois (ENSIIE Paris, France)=20

=C2=B7 Kerstin Eder (University of Bristol, UK)=20

=C2=B7 Tias Guns (University of Brussel, Belgium)=20

=C2=B7 A lexey Ignatiev (Monash University, Australia)=20

=C2=B7 Felix Ingrand (LAAS-CNRS, Toulouse, France)=20

=C2=B7 Laurent Simon (LABRI, Bordeaux, France)=20




Early registration (before March 16, 2020 for the preregistration and befor=
e April 15, 2020 for the final registration) is encouraged. The number of p=
articipants is limited to 30. For further information, please contact Nadji=
b Lazaar (lazaar@lirmm.fr).=20




VIVA 2020 Registration Fees=20




=E2=80=A2 Type of room: Single room with shared sanitary facilities=20

=E2=80=A2 Before April 15, 2020 : 600 =E2=82=AC=20

=E2=80=A2 After April 15, 2020 : 700 =E2=82=AC=20







Your registration includes:=20

=C2=B7 5 nights (from June 14, 2020 to June 19, 2020) at Belambra resort=20

=C2=B7 5 breakfasts=20

=C2=B7 5 lunches=20

=C2=B7 3 dinners and 1 gala dinner=20

=C2=B7 Coffee-breaks=20

=C2=B7 One social event=20

=C2=B7 Access to all the plenaries and training labs=20

=C2=B7 Goodies=20







Registration=20




Registration is a two-step procedure:=20




STEP 1=20




For application, please submit one pdf including your CV + a cover letter (=
before March 16, 2020) on Easychair (https://easychair.org/my/conference?co=
nf=3Dviva2020).=20

A scientific committee will select the applications and notification of acc=
eptance will be sent on March 20, 2020 . Criteria such as Research interest=
 and motivations of the candidate,=20

gender and geographical balance will be considered.=20




Once your application is accepted, proceed to step 2.=20




STEP 2=20

Register and pay online using the registration form used in the acceptance =
notification.=20







Terms and conditions for sponsorships : any student registered in a PhD pro=
gram in Norway at the time of application can apply for sponsorship. Partic=
ipating students will be selected by the scientific committee of the school=
. Applicants should follow the standard application procedure given above.=
=20

Registration fees will be waived for selected applicants only. Travel expen=
ses will be covered.=20







For administrative and financial questions, please contact M=C3=A9gane Miqu=
el (megane.miquel@lirmm.fr).=20







Best regards,=20

Nadjib, Arnaud and Florent=20









--=20
Florent MASSEGLIA - Inria Research Scientist - Zenith Team=20

